title: For Sale:  1942 Ex-PEM Sniper M91/30
postcontent:
I have a 1942 Mosin Nagant Ex-PEM sniper M91/30 for sale. 
Comes with Bayonet, Ammo pouch, and tool kit
Will add surplus ammo for extra money. 100 for $25, 200 for $50, or 440 for $100
This rifle does have the holes in the reciever from the PEM scope mount plugged, and scope number has been struck out in the barrel shank.
For a little History, in WW2 after Germany invaded Russia, the Russian military found thier SVT-40 sniper rifles had accuracy issues. to quickly arm thier front line snipers the Russian started back up production of PEM snipers in 1942, until they had adapted the PU scopes for the mosin nagant snipers in late 1942. 
By the end of WW2 Russia had way too many snipers, so they kept a portion of thier PU snipers, while returning the rest, and older sniper variants back into regular M91/30s
 
Looking to sell or trade for other milsurps, or milsurps with minor sporterizations. 
Also looking for a good quality 22LR bolt action rifle.

title: For Sale:  NEW Dan Wesson 715 Target 6" 357MAG
postcontent: ASK ABOUT OUR 60-DAY LAY-A-WAY!For Sale is a NEW Dan Wesson 715 357MAG Revolver.  Read below for product description and link to the DW website.  As always, you must be legally allowed to own this pistol and capable of passing a FBI NICS Background Check.  We take Cash, Check, VISA, MasterCard, and Discover.  We will ship anywhere in the ConUSA for $30.  Thanks for looking!http://cz-usa.com/product/dan-wesson-715-revolver-cal-357-magnum-stainless/ The 715 is as it was before — designed and built to be the most accurate, rugged and versatile revolver on the market. Shipped with a 6″ barrel, the new shroud is designated the HV6, a heavy vent shroud profile that tames the .357’s recoil very well. The double action trigger is short and relatively light, while the single action is light and crisp. The target-like SA trigger pull made the Dan Wesson revolver a favorite among competitors and hunters, and the tradition continues in the 715. Barrel assemblies and grips are easily swapped by the shooter, and the 715 accepts grips and barrel/shroud assemblies from 15-2 model and newer revolvers. The original Dan Wesson revolver improved on the accuracy and service life of the traditional double action revolver design in a few ways. The tensioned barrel of the DW interchangeable barrel system enhances accuracy, pulling the barrel tight like a guitar string, enabling it to vibrate at the same frequency every time. The forward crane latch, located in front of the cylinder and paired with a rear ball detent helps to ensure proper cylinder/barrel alignment during firing. Superior to the rear locking designs of other revolvers, it adds to the accuracy of the 715. While the tensioned barrel definitely improves accuracy above other revolvers, it’s the consistent cylinder/barrel alignment that contributes most to the accuracy of the design. Additionally, the clockwise-rotating cylinder reduces stress on the crane, since it turns in the same direction the crane locks, prolonging service life and keeping everything tight. The 715’s frame is robust, built to handle the heaviest of factory loads. Each revolver is shipped in a custom Dan Wesson hard case. Patterned after the ever-popular Pistol Pack, each case has compartments for three additional barrel assemblies and factory-supplied barrel wrench kit. The 715 Pistol Pack ships with 4″, 6″ and 8″ barrel lengths.
